Rating: 4
Made 1/2 recipe for my wife and I. Wife gave me the keys to the stove for this one. We were low on green onions and added about 2 tablespoons of diced tomato. Also, used fresh Boar's head smoked deli turkey (1/4 pound) in place of the sausage. Garnished with red grapes. Added a slice of fresh whole grain bread to the garnishment, as well. This is a definite brunch type preparation. It took less than 15 minutes to prepare, about 5 to eat. Delicious.

